Package propertytycoon

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Agent
    The automated agent that plays the game for any player set to 'Auto'
    Card
    The Card class represents a card on the Opportunity Knocks or Pot-Luck piles
    CardSpace
    The CardSpace class represents a board space that requires the player to take a card
    GameController
    The GameController provides methods that the GUI can call to start the game and to process the latest player choice.
    GameModel
    The GameModel class is the top-level class for all game data.
    GoSpace
    The GoSpace represents the GO space on the board
    GUI_2
    This class implements the game user interface
    Instruction
    The Instruction class is used by the RulesProvider to instruct the GameModel to modify the model state
    InstructionSpace
    This class represents board spaces that contain instructions for the player to follow
    JailSpace
    Represents the 'Jail' space on the board
    Main
    The main entry point of the application Loads the initial game model static from the spreadsheet then creates the game controller and the GUI
    Player
    This class contains data for the state of the player
    PlayerOption
    The PlayerOption class represents one of the various options that the player if offered at each stage of the game.
    PlayerOptionResponse
    This class holds the option that the player has selected
    Property
    The property class holds the state of each property including the static data loaded at the start of the game
    PropertySpace
    This class represents a board space holding a property
    RuleProvider
    The RuleProvider class contains all rules for the game.
    RuleResult
    This class holds the options and instructions returned by the RuleProvider
    Space
    This is the superclass representing all board spaces
    UserChoiceRequest
    This class contains the player options for the next step of the game.
    UserChoiceResponse
    This class contains the selected player option from the GUI sent when the go button is clicked
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CardType
    Represents the possible card types
    GameStageType
    Represents the various stages of the game during a player's turn
    InstructionType
    These are the various types of instructions
    PlayerOptionType
    These are the various option types
    PlayerTokenType
    The tokens representing the game players
    PropertyGroupColour
    These are the property group colours
    PropertyType
    These are the various property types
